.TH SUDOERS "1" "December 2025" "202602020740-git" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
sudoers \- Add and remove users from sudo
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B sudoers
[\fI\,OPTIONS\/\fR] [\fI\,add\/\fR|\fI\,remove\/\fR] [\fI\,USERNAME\/\fR]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B sudoers
is a script for managing sudo access for users. It provides a simple interface to add or remove users from the sudo group.
.PP
The script handles the necessary system commands to modify sudo permissions.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.BR \-\-help
Display help message with usage information and available options
.TP
.BR \-\-config
Generate or regenerate user configuration file with default settings
.TP
.BR \-\-version
Show script version information and exit
.TP
.BR \-\-options
Display all available command-line options
.TP
.BR \-\-debug
Enable debug mode with verbose output and command tracing (set -x)
.TP
.BR \-\-raw
Disable colorized output for plain text display
.SH COMMANDS
.TP
.B add USERNAME
Add user to sudo group
.TP
.B remove USERNAME
Remove user from sudo group
.SH EXAMPLES
.TP
.B sudoers add john
Grant sudo access to user john
.TP
.B sudoers remove john
Revoke sudo access from user john
.SH FILES
.TP
.B ~/.config/myscripts/sudoers/settings.conf
User configuration file for sudoers preferences
.TP
.B /etc/sudoers.d/
System sudoers configuration directory
.SH EXIT STATUS
.TP
.B 0
Success
.TP
.B 1
General error
.TP
.B 2
Permission denied (requires root)
.SH NOTES
.IP \(bu 2
Requires root privileges
.IP \(bu 2
Modifies system sudo configuration
.IP \(bu 2
Use with caution
